# Rudniki, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Rudniki () is a rural locality (a village) in Kalininsky Selsoviet, Bizhbulyaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 3 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Rudniki is located 28 km northeast of Bizhbulyak (the district's administrative centre) by road. Tumash is the nearest rural locality.
